.TH YAML_OUTPUT_PENDING 3 "2026-06-30" "libyaml 0.1.0" "libyaml library"
.SH NAME
yaml_output_pending, yaml_output_size \- serializer output buffer queries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <yaml.h>
.PP
.BI "size_t yaml_output_pending(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.BI "size_t yaml_output_size(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR yaml_output_pending ()
returns the number of bytes currently buffered in the serializer output.
For a parser context or a NULL context, returns 0.
This is useful to determine the required buffer size before calling
.BR yaml_get_output ().
.PP
.BR yaml_output_size ()
is an alias for
.BR yaml_output_pending ()
and returns the same value. Both functions query the same internal buffer.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Both functions return the number of buffered output bytes as a
.IR size_t .
Returns 0 if the context is NULL, the role is not
.BR YAML_ROLE_SERIALIZER ,
or the output buffer is empty.
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
/* Emit some events */
yaml_emit_mapping_start(s, NULL, NULL);
yaml_emit_scalar(s, "key", 3, NULL, YAML_SCALAR_PLAIN);
yaml_emit_mapping_end(s);

/* Check output size before draining */
size_t sz = yaml_output_pending(s);
uint8_t *buf = malloc(sz);
yaml_get_output(s, buf, sz);
.fi
.SH THREAD SAFETY
Not thread-safe. Use from a single thread at a time.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yaml_get_output (3),
.BR yaml_emit_scalar (3),
.BR yaml_emit_mapping_start (3)
